<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:rng="http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0"
  xmlns:sch="http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron"
  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
  xml:lang="en">
  <teiHeader>
    <fileDesc>
      <titleStmt>
        <title>HSP-TEI P5 Customization and Encoding Guidelines for Manuscript Description</title>
        <author xml:id="geissel">Pia Geißel</author>
        <author xml:id="schassan">Torsten Schaßan</author>
      </titleStmt>
      <publicationStmt>
        <publisher>TEI Consortium</publisher>
        <availability status="free">
          <p>This template file is freely available and you are hereby authorised to copy, modify,
            and redistribute it in any way without further reference or permissions.</p>
          <p>When making such modifications, you are strongly recommended to change the present text
            to include an accurate statement of the licensing conditions applicable to your modified
            text.</p>
        </availability>
      </publicationStmt>
      <notesStmt>
        <note>Basic parts of the description are taken from the TEI Guidelines.</note>
        <note>Additional description added from Medieval Manuscripts in Oxford Libraries: TEI
          catalogue descriptions on GitHub <ref target="https://github.com/bodleian/medieval-mss"
          /></note>
        <note>Description follows the Richtlinien Handschriftenkatalogisierung of Deutsche
          Forschungsgemeinschaft <ref
            target="http://bilder.manuscripta-mediaevalia.de/hs//kataloge/HSKRICH.htm"/>
        </note>
      </notesStmt>
      <sourceDesc>
        <p>Initially created on <date when="2020-06-03">3.6.2020</date> by the form at
          http://www.tei-c.org.uk/Roma/.</p>
      </sourceDesc>
    </fileDesc>
  </teiHeader>
  <text>
    <front>
      <divGen type="toc" xml:id="toc"/>
      <div xml:id="introduction">
        <head>Introductory remarks</head>
        <p>These Guidelines describe the structure of manuscript descriptions according to the rules
          of the German <ref target="https://handschriftenportal.de">Handschriftenportal</ref>
            (<abbr>HSP</abbr>). This document serves a threefold purpose: <list>
            <item>The text of the Guidelines describe the cataloguing principles, all parts of a
              catalogue document, and all aspects of a manuscript description in accordance with the
              German cataloguing rules. The text also explains the usage of the description in the
              scope of the <soCalled>Handschriftenportal</soCalled>, especially why some information
              has to be recorded in a certain manner because it might be needed for some
              functionality in the portal.</item>
            <item>The examples included in the Guidelines show the way, how the cataloguing rules
              result in valid TEI markup. The TEI format is the preferred format of the import and
              export of manuscript related information. All descriptions that shall be imported into
              the portal need to be structured in compliance with these Guidelines. Exports from the
              portal will be supplied first of all in the format of TEI-encoded documents. Library
              metadata such as MARC records will be described in other documents.</item>
            <item>This document will provide a formal definition of all elements, attributes and
              structures that are allowed and expected in the resulting TEI files. The appendices
              will contain a detailed description of the technical aspects of the cataloguing
              rules.</item>
          </list> This document will result in an updated version of the cataloguing guidelines of
          the DFG, which in its latest edition date back to 1992.</p>
        <p>Although the document is written from scratch, it has its predecessors in an
            <abbr>ODD</abbr> written for the manuscript cataloguing in the Herzog August Bibliothek
          Wolfenbüttel, in papers written in the scope of the <bibl>Europeana Regia project</bibl>
            (<ref target="http://www.hab.de/files/europeana-regia/ODD/europeana-regia.xml"
          >ODD</ref>, <bibl>D2.3 Vademecum for librarians, <ref
              target="http://diglib.hab.de/rules/documentation/ER/v1.1/Europeana-Regia_D2.3_Vademecum-for-librarians.pdf"
              >PDF</ref></bibl>, and an ODD written at the Bodleian Library Oxford.</p>
        <p>Technically, this document is encoded as a <abbr>TEI</abbr>
          <abbr>ODD</abbr> file. <abbr>ODD</abbr> is the abbreviation of <expan>One Document Does it
            all</expan>. An ODD file contains all information in a human and a machine readable
          way.</p>
      </div>
    </front>
    <body>
      <div xml:id="encodingGuidelines">
        <head>Encoding Guidelines</head>
        <p>As the <abbr>HSP</abbr> will combine information about manuscripts and display records
          from different repositories, the quality and depth of the descriptions may differ. In
          order to gain control over the different kinds of records, this guideline provides rules
          for descriptions of manuscripts. At the same time they intend to replace the current
          guidelines <bibl>Richtlinien Handschriftenkatalogisierung der DFG</bibl>.</p>
        <p>The base entity of the HSP is a <soCalled>Kulturobject</soCalled> (<soCalled>cultural
            object</soCalled>. Cultural objects are any real world objects in the scope of the HSP.
          These will be manuscripts in the first place but as well objects like former manuscript
          bindings. The HSP establishes one <soCalled>Kulturobjektdokument</soCalled>
            (<soCalled>cultural object document</soCalled>, <abbr>KOD</abbr>) as representation for
          each cultural object. This <abbr>KOD</abbr> serves as an anchor for all data and
          descriptions concerning a single manuscript. After a registration at the website a user, a
          repository or an institution can now add their own information to a manuscript e.g.
          measure, material, content and history or even a digital copy of the object. This approach
          ensures that the <abbr>KOD</abbr> in its current state can be altered and be aligned
          towards new approaches and scientific findings. </p>
        <p>To identify and individualise a manuscript the <abbr>HSP</abbr> generates a minimal data
          set, <soCalled>Minimaldatensatz</soCalled>, consisting of <list>
            <item>the place of the institution the object belongs to,</item>
            <item>the name of the institution the object belongs to and</item>
            <item>the current, normalised shelfmark of the object.</item>
          </list> Alternative identifications of the object, such as variant writings of the current
          shelfmark, former shelfmarks, catalogue numbers, or sigla within editions, may be added to
          the minimal data.</p>
        <p>Each object is assigned with a unique ID in the <abbr>HSP</abbr>. Once the Deutsche
          Nationalbibliothek has assigned a unique identifier for each
            <soCalled>Schriftdenkmal</soCalled> in the <soCalled>Gemeinsame Normdatei</soCalled>
            (<abbr>GND</abbr>), the GND-ID will be referenced as well. The
            <soCalled>Schriftdenkmal</soCalled> is in the scope of the <abbr>HSP</abbr> identical to
          the <soCalled>Kulturobject</soCalled>.</p>
        <p>On a supplementary basis, the following core data is recommended for each object: <list>
            <item>a brief descriptive title,</item>
            <item>material(s),</item>
            <item>the dimensions of the object,</item>
            <item>the number of leaves or pages,</item>
            <item>the date(s) of origin,</item>
            <item>the place(s) of origin,</item>
            <item>the written language(s),</item>
            <item>the occurence of decoration description,</item>
            <item>the occurence of music notations,</item>
            <item>the form of the object (e.g. codex, fragment),</item>
            <item>the current status of the object (e.g. extant, destroyed, missing).</item>
          </list>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="head_date">
        <head>How to date a manuscript</head>
        <figure>
          <table rend="boxed" rows="14" cols="4" style="width:100%">
            <row>
              <cell role="label">time</cell>
              <cell role="label">timespan</cell>
              <cell role="label">XML-example</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>9. Jh.</cell>
              <cell>801-900</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0801"
                    notAfter="0900">9. Jh.</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>9. Jh., 1. Hälfte</cell>
              <cell>801-850</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0801"
                    notAfter="0850">9. Jh., 1. Hälfte</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>9. Jh., 2. Hälfte</cell>
              <cell>851-900</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0851"
                    notAfter="900">9. Jh., 2. Hälfte</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>9. Jh., 1. Drittel</cell>
              <cell>801-833</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0801"
                    notAfter="0833">9. Jh., 1. Drittel</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>9. Jh., 1. Viertel</cell>
              <cell>801-825</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0701"
                    notAfter="0725">9.Jh., 1. Viertel</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>9. Jh., Anfang</cell>
              <cell>801-815</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0801"
                    notAfter="0815">9. Jh., Anfang</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>9. Jh., Mitte</cell>
              <cell>841-860</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0841"
                    notAfter="0860">9. Jh., Mitte</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>9. Jh., Ende</cell>
              <cell>-15 years, 886-900</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0886"
                    notAfter="0900">9. Jh., Ende</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>vor 800</cell>
              <cell>-14 years, 786-799</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0786"
                    notAfter="0799">vor 800</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>nach 800</cell>
              <cell>+15 years, 801-815</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0801"
                    notAfter="0815">nach 800</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>um 800</cell>
              <cell>±15 years, 786-815</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><origDate notBefore="0786"
                    notAfter="0815">um 800</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>8./9. Jh</cell>
              <cell>±10 years, 791-810</cell>
              <cell><egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                  <origDate notBefore="0791" notAfter="0810">8./9. Jh.</origDate></egXML></cell>
            </row>
          </table>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="index-Term">
        <head>The Index-Elements</head>
        <p>In addition to the <gi>head</gi> element, the <soCalled>Schlagzeile</soCalled> is
          required to fill in the essential informations in <gi>term</gi> elements. The setup has
          the following structure: <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
            <head>
              <index indexName="norm_title">
                <term type="title">__normalized title of the Manuscript__</term>
              </index>
              <title>__The title of the manuscript__</title>
              <note type="headline">__the headline of the manuscript__</note>
              <index indexName="norm_material">
                <term type="material">__material of the manuscript__</term>
                <term type="material_type">__select from value list__</term>
                <term type="material_type">__select from value list__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_measure">
                <term type="measure">__number of leaves__</term>
                <term type="measure_noOfLeaves">__quantity of the leaves__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_dimensions">
                <term type="dimensions">__dimension of the manuscript__</term>
                <term type="height">__height of the manuscript__</term>
                <term type="width">__width of the manuscript__</term>
                <term type="depth">__depth of the manuscript__</term>
                <term type="dimensions_typeOfInformation">__type of information__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_format">
                <term type="format">__select from value list__</term>
                <term type="format_typeOfInformation">__type of information__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_origPlace">
                <term type="origPlace">__place where the manuscript originated from__</term>
                <term type="origPlace_norm" ref="http://dnb.indo/XXXX-X" key="UU-ID">__normalized name__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_origDate">
                <term type="origDate">__the presumable date__</term>
                <term type="origDate_notBefore">__narrowing the century__</term>
                <term type="origDate_notAfter">__narrowing the century__</term>
                <term type="origDate_type">__select from value list__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_textLang">
                <term type="textLang">__main Language of the manuscript</term>
                <term type="textLang-ID">ID of the language (ISO-norm)</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_form">
                <term type="form">__select from value list__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_status">
                <term type="status">__select from value list__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_decoration">
                <term type="decoration">__select from value list__</term>
              </index>
              <index indexName="norm_musicNotation">
                <term type="musicNotation">__select from value list__</term>
              </index>
            </head>
          </egXML>
        </p>
      </div>


      <div xml:id="formalDecl">
        <head>Formal Declarations</head>
        <schemaSpec ident="hsp_cataloguing" xml:lang="en" targetLang="en" docLang="en">
          <moduleRef key="tei"/>
          <moduleRef key="textstructure" include="TEI text body div front back"/>
          <moduleRef key="header" include="
            availability
            change correspAction correspContext correspDesc creation
            distributor
            edition editionStmt encodingDesc extent 
            fileDesc funder 
            handNote
            idno 
            keywords
            langUsage language licence listChange listPrefixDef 
            profileDesc projectDesc publicationStmt 
            rendition revisionDesc 
            scriptNote seriesStmt sourceDesc sponsor  
            taxonomy teiHeader textClass titleStmt"/>
          <moduleRef key="core" include="
            abbr add author 
            bibl biblScope 
            cb choice cit citedRange corr 
            date del desc 
            editor emph expan 
            foreign 
            gap gb graphic 
            head headItem headLabel hi 
            index item 
            l label lb lg list listBibl 
            measure measureGrp mentioned milestone 
            name note num 
            orig 
            p pb ptr pubPlace publisher 
            quote 
            ref reg relatedItem resp respStmt rs 
            series sic soCalled 
            teiCorpus term textLang time title 
            unclear unit"/>
          <moduleRef key="msdescription" include="
            accMat acquisition additional additions adminInfo altIdentifier 
            binding bindingDesc 
            catchwords collation collection colophon condition custEvent custodialHist 
            decoDesc decoNote depth dim dimensions 
            explicit 
            filiation finalRubric foliation 
            handDesc height heraldry history 
            incipit institution 
            layout layoutDesc locus locusGrp 
            material msContents msDesc msFrag msIdentifier msItem msName msPart musicNotation 
            objectDesc objectType origDate origPlace origin 
            physDesc provenance 
            recordHist repository rubric 
            scriptDesc seal sealDesc secFol signatures source stamp summary support supportDesc surrogates 
            typeDesc typeNote 
            watermark width"/>
          <moduleRef key="namesdates" include="
            addName affiliation age 
            birth 
            country 
            death 
            education event 
            faith floruit forename 
            genName geo 
            listEvent listObject listOrg listPerson listPlace listRelation location 
            nameLink nationality 
            object objectIdentifier objectName occupation org orgName 
            persName person personGrp place placeName 
            region relation residence roleName 
            settlement sex surname"/>
          <moduleRef key="figures" include="
            cell 
            figDesc figure formula 
            notatedMusic 
            row 
            table"/>
          <moduleRef key="gaiji" include="
            g
            unicodeName unicodeProp"/>
          <moduleRef key="transcr" include="
            ex 
            facsimile fw 
            supplied surface surfaceGrp 
            zone"/>
          <moduleRef key="analysis" include="
            w"/>
          <moduleRef key="iso-fs" include="
            binary 
            f fs 
            symbol"/>
          <specGrpRef target="#classmods"/>
          <specGrpRef target="#bodyfixes"/>
          <specGrpRef target="#hdrfixes"/>
          <specGrpRef target="#msdescfixes"/>
          <classRef key="att.global.facs"/>
          <classRef key="att.global.linking"/>
          <classRef key="att.canonical"/>
          <dataSpec ident="teidata.temporal.iso" mode="delete"/>

          <!-- header Fixes -->
          <elementSpec ident="sourceDesc" mode="change" module="header">
            <desc>Descriptive text here </desc>
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="default" mode="delete"/>
            </attList>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- body fixes-->
          <specGrp xml:id="bodyfixes">
            <elementSpec ident="title" mode="change" module="core">
              <attList>
                <attDef ident="level" mode="delete"/>
              </attList>
            </elementSpec>
          </specGrp>

          <!-- ############################################  Specifications body ##########################################################  -->

          <!-- element specification altIdentifier - Komponente Identifikation (altIdentifier)-->
          <elementSpec ident="altIdentifier" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="req">
                <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                  <valItem ident="corpus">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">corpus shelf number</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Identifikator</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="former">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">former shelf number</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">ehemalige Signatur</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="hsp-ID">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">hsp-Kulturobjektdokument-ID</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">hsp-Kulturobjektdokument-ID</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="mxml-ID">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">Manuscripta-Medievalia-ID</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Manuscripta-Medievalia-ID</desc>
                  </valItem>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
            </attList>
            <exemplum>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                <msDesc status="extern" xml:id="HSP-4f5fe1f5-938c-329b-8f83-b7521f4806ac"
                  xml:lang="de" subtype="medieval" type="hsp:description">
                  <msIdentifier>
                    <settlement key="soz_123456789">Karlsruhe</settlement>
                    <repository key="soz_30002072"
                      ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/2005707-6 https://sigel.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/suche/?isil=DE-31"
                      >Badische Landesbibliothek</repository>
                    <idno>Cod. Karlsruhe 2912, II A 1, a</idno>
                    <altIdentifier type="hsp-ID">
                      <collection>Handschriftenportal Kulturobjektdokument-ID</collection>
                      <idno>HSP_123456-a7891234-a56789</idno>
                    </altIdentifier>
                    <altIdentifier type="mxml-ID">
                      <collection>Manuscripta-Medievalia-ID</collection>
                      <idno>obj_123456</idno>
                    </altIdentifier>
                    <altIdentifier type="corpus">
                      <collection>collection XYZ</collection>
                      <idno>123</idno>
                    </altIdentifier>
                    <altIdentifier type="former">
                      <settlement key="26cf9267-82fe-3bf1-a37-c9960658499f">Regensburg</settlement>
                      <repository key="654a4abc-3191-3e68-995b-4fdbd157cf9d">Sankt
                        Emmeran</repository>
                      <idno>St. Emm 57</idno>
                    </altIdentifier>
                  </msIdentifier>
                </msDesc>
              </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification date -->
          <elementSpec ident="date" mode="change" module="core">
            <constraintSpec ident="dateSchematronConstraint" scheme="schematron">
              <desc>Constraint for <gi>date</gi> in <gi>surrogates</gi></desc>
              <constraint>
                <sch:pattern id="isoNormDate">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:surrogates/tei:bibl/tei:date">
                    <sch:assert test="@when[matches(.,'^[1,2]\d{3}-[0,1]\d{1}-\d{2}$')]"> @when
                      requires a date in the standard form: yyyy-mm-dd. </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
            <!-- deleted due to incompatibility 
              <constraintSpec ident="date_check" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <sch:pattern>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:date">
                    <sch:assert test="@when or (@notAfter and @notBefore) or (@from and @to)">You
                      must provide either @when or @to/@from, or @notAfter/@notBefore.</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
            -->
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="when" mode="change" usage="rec"/>
              <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="rec">
                <valList mode="change" type="semi">
                  <valItem ident="primary"/>
                  <valItem ident="secondary"/>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
            </attList>
          </elementSpec>


          <!--element specification decoDesc -Komponente Äußeres Kunst -->
          <elementSpec ident="decoDesc" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <content>
              <rng:oneOrMore>
                <rng:ref name="decoNote"/>
              </rng:oneOrMore>
            </content>
            <exemplum>
              <p>decoDesc may be used when specifying a description of some illuminated aspects of a
                manuscript, otherwise it is to be described in msContents</p>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                <phsyDesc>
                  <p>formal physical description</p>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="form"> insert the description of some illuminated aspects of a
                      manuscript here </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                </phsyDesc>
              </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification decoNote Komponente Äußeres Kunst und Inhalt Kunst -->
          <elementSpec ident="decoNote" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <constraintSpec ident="contraintdecoNote" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <sch:pattern id="ÄußeresKunst">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:physDesc/tei:decoDesc/tei:decoNote">
                    <sch:assert test="@type eq 'form' "> It's possible to describe some illuminated
                      aspects of a manuscript here </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="type" mode="replace" usage="req">
                <valList type="closed">
                  <valItem ident="form"/>
                  <valItem ident="content"/>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
            </attList>
            <exemplum>
              <p>decoDesc may be used when specifying a description of some illuminated aspects of a
                manuscript, otherwise it is to be described in msContents</p>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                <phsyDesc>
                  <p>formal physical description</p>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="form"> insert the description of some illuminated aspects of a
                      manuscript here </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                </phsyDesc>
              </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification head - Komponente Kopf -->
          <!-- head content specifications moved to msDesc due to incompatibility with head in listbibl -->
          <elementSpec ident="head" module="core" mode="change">
            <constraintSpec ident="head" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <sch:pattern id="indexTermHead">
                  <!-- <sch:rule context="tei:term[@type eq 'title']">
                    <sch:assert test="normalize-space()">Should contain a title</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>-->
                  <!-- material -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msDesc/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'material_type']">
                    <sch:assert test=".= ('','paper','linen','palm','papyrus','parchment','other')">
                      If type="material_type", text should contain 'paper', 'linen', 'palm',
                      'papyrus', 'parchment', 'other' or should stay empty. </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!--measure-->
                  <!--<sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'measure']">
                    <sch:assert test="normalize-space()">Should contain the number of leaves e.g. 12
                      Bl.</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>-->
                  <sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'measure_noOfLeaves']">
                    <sch:assert test=".[matches(.,'^[0-9]*?$')]">The content may only contain
                      numbers</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!--dimensions-->
                  <!--<sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'dimensions']">
                    <sch:assert test="normalize-space()">Should contain the dimension of the
                      manuscript e.g 30,5 × 22</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>-->
                  <sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type='height']">
                    <sch:assert test=".[matches(.,'^([0-9]+(,5)?)?$')]">Value of height may only be
                      an integer or must be a float which ends with ,5 or is empty</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type='width']">
                    <sch:assert test=".[matches(.,'^([0-9]+(,5)?)?$')]">Value of width may only be
                      an integer or must be a float which ends with ,5 or is empty</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type='depth']">
                    <sch:assert test=".[matches(.,'^([0-9]+(,5)?)?$')]">Value of depth may only be
                      an integer or must be a float which ends with ,5 or is empty</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:term[@type='dimensions_typeOfInformation']">
                    <sch:assert test=". =('','deduced','factual')"> If
                      type="dimensions_typeOfInformation" then content should be 'deduced' or
                      'factual' or should stay empty. </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!-- format -->
                  <sch:rule context="tei:term[@type='format']">
                    <sch:assert
                      test=".= ('','folio','quarto','octavo','smaller than octavo','larger than folio','other','oblong','square','long and narrow')"
                      > folio, quarto, octavo, other, smaller than octavo, larger than folio,
                      oblong, long and narrow, square or empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:term[@type='format_typeOfInformation']">
                    <sch:assert test=".=('','deduced','factual', 'computed')"> deduced, factual or
                      empty. </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!--origDate-->
                  <sch:rule context="tei:term[@type='origDate_type']">
                    <sch:assert test=". = ('','dated','datable')"> If type="origDate_type", content
                      should be dated or datable or empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type='origDate_notBefore']">
                    <sch:assert
                      test=".[matches(.,'^((\-?[0-9]{4}\-(0[1-9]|1[012])\-(0[1-9]|[12][0-9]|3[01]))|(\-?[0-9]{4}\-(0[1-9]|1[012]))|(\-?[0-9]{4}))?$')]"
                      > The content should contain a date (year); several date-types are allowed:
                      YYYY-MM-DD, -YYYY-MM-DD, YYYY-MM , -YYYY-MM or YYYY.</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type='origDate_notAfter']">
                    <sch:assert
                      test=".[matches(.,'^((\-?[0-9]{4}\-(0[1-9]|1[012])\-(0[1-9]|[12][0-9]|3[01]))|(\-?[0-9]{4}\-(0[1-9]|1[012]))|(\-?[0-9]{4}))?$')]"
                      > The content should contain a date (year); several date-types are allowed:
                      YYYY-MM-DD, -YYYY-MM-DD, YYYY-MM , -YYYY-MM or YYYY. </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!--form-->
                  <sch:rule context="tei:msDesc/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'form']">
                    <sch:assert
                      test=".= ('', 'codex', 'collection', 'composite', 'leporello', 'sammelband', 'fragment', 'printWithManuscriptParts', 'hostVolume', 'singleSheet', 'scroll', 'other')"
                      > If @type="form", Text should contain 'codex', 'collection', 'composite',
                      'leporello', 'sammelband', 'fragment', 'singleSheet',
                      'printWithManuscriptParts', 'hostVolume', 'scroll', 'other' or should stay
                      empty</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!-- status-->
                  <sch:rule context="tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'status']">
                    <sch:assert
                      test=". = ('','missing','existent','destroyed','dismembered','unknown','displaced')"
                      > If @type="status", content should be: 'existent', 'missing', 'destroyed',
                      'unknown','displaced' or should stay empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!--decoration and musicNotation-->
                  <sch:rule context="tei:term[@type='decoration']">
                    <sch:assert test=". =('','yes','no')"> If type="decoration" then content should
                      be 'yes' or 'no' or empty</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:term[@type='musicNotation']">
                    <sch:assert test=". =('','yes','no')"> If type="musicNotation" then content
                      should be 'yes' or 'no' or empty.</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
          </elementSpec>


          <!-- element specification history - Komponente Geschichte -->
          <elementSpec ident="history" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <content>
              <elementRef key="p" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>
            </content>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification idno -->
          <elementSpec ident="idno" mode="change" module="header">
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="sortKey" mode="change" usage="opt"/>
            </attList>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification msContents Komponente Inhalt (Text, Musik, Kunst, Äußeres Kunst)  -->
          <elementSpec ident="msContents" mode="change" module="msdescription">
            <content>
              <elementRef key="textLang" minOccurs="0"/>
              <elementRef key="msItem" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>
            </content>
            <exemplum>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="de" otherLangs="la fr">Handschrift enthält Texte in Deutsch,
                    Latein und Französisch</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                    <note type="text">Inhalt Text Abschnitt</note>
                    <decoNote type="content">Inhalt Kunst</decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="form">Äußeres Kunst</decoNote>
                    <msItem>
                      <note type="text"> Inhalt Text untergeordneter Abschnitt</note>
                    </msItem>
                  </msItem>
                </msContents>
              </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>


          <!-- element specification msDesc -->
          <elementSpec ident="msDesc" mode="change" module="msdescription">
            <content>
              <rng:ref name="msIdentifier"/>
              <!-- ODD 0.7.0 sequence ist recommended, due to compatibility to 0.6.1 every sequence is allowed so far by interleaving  -->
              <rng:element name="head">
                <rng:interleave>
                  <!-- title norm-->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_title</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>title</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:optional>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:optional>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:element>
                  <!-- title -->
                  <rng:element name="title">
                    <rng:zeroOrMore>
                      <rng:choice>
                        <rng:element name="hi">
                          <rng:attribute name="rend">
                            <rng:choice>
                              <rng:value>italic</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>italic sup</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>italic line-through</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>small-caps</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>sup small-caps</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>sup</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>sub</rng:value>
                            </rng:choice>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:text/>
                        </rng:element>
                        <rng:element name="lb"/>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:choice>
                    </rng:zeroOrMore>
                  </rng:element>
                  <!-- note -->
                  <rng:element name="note">
                    <rng:attribute name="type">
                      <rng:value>headline</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:zeroOrMore>
                      <rng:choice>
                        <rng:element name="hi">
                          <rng:attribute name="rend">
                            <rng:choice>
                              <rng:value>italic</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>italic sup</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>italic line-through</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>small-caps</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>sup small-caps</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>sup</rng:value>
                              <rng:value>sub</rng:value>
                            </rng:choice>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:text/>
                        </rng:element>
                        <rng:element name="lb"/>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:choice>
                    </rng:zeroOrMore>
                  </rng:element>
                </rng:interleave>


                <rng:oneOrMore>
                  <!-- material -->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_material</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>material</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                    <!-- wdh -->
                    <rng:oneOrMore>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>material_type</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                    </rng:oneOrMore>
                  </rng:element>

                  <!-- measure -->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_measure</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>measure</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>measure_noOfLeaves</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:element>

                  <!-- dimensions wdh -->
                  <rng:oneOrMore>
                    <rng:element name="index">
                      <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                        <rng:value>norm_dimensions</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>dimensions</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>height</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>width</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                      <rng:zeroOrMore>
                        <rng:element name="term">
                          <rng:attribute name="type">
                            <rng:value>depth</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:text/>
                        </rng:element>
                      </rng:zeroOrMore>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>dimensions_typeOfInformation</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:oneOrMore>

                  <!-- format wdh -->
                  <rng:oneOrMore>
                    <rng:element name="index">
                      <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                        <rng:value>norm_format</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>format</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>format_typeOfInformation</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:oneOrMore>

                  <!-- origPlace wdh -->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_origPlace</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>origPlace</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                    <!-- wdh. -->
                    <rng:oneOrMore>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>origPlace_norm</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:optional>
                          <rng:attribute name="ref"/>
                        </rng:optional>
                        <rng:optional>
                          <rng:attribute name="key"/>
                        </rng:optional>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                    </rng:oneOrMore>
                  </rng:element>

                  <!-- origDate -->
                  <rng:oneOrMore>
                    <rng:element name="index">
                      <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                        <rng:value>norm_origDate</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>origDate</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                      <!-- als Block -->
                      <rng:group>
                        <rng:element name="term">
                          <rng:attribute name="type">
                            <rng:value>origDate_notBefore</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:text/>
                        </rng:element>
                        <rng:element name="term">
                          <rng:attribute name="type">
                            <rng:value>origDate_notAfter</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:text/>
                        </rng:element>
                        <rng:element name="term">
                          <rng:attribute name="type">
                            <rng:value>origDate_type</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:text/>
                        </rng:element>
                      </rng:group>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:oneOrMore>

                  <!-- textLang -->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_textLang</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>textLang</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                    <!-- wdh. -->
                    <rng:oneOrMore>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>textLang-ID</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                    </rng:oneOrMore>
                  </rng:element>

                  <!-- form -->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_form</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>form</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:element>

                  <!-- status -->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_status</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>status</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:element>

                  <!-- decoration -->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_decoration</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>decoration</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:element>

                  <!-- musicNotation -->
                  <rng:element name="index">
                    <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                      <rng:value>norm_musicNotation</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <rng:element name="term">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:value>musicNotation</rng:value>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:element>
                </rng:oneOrMore>
              </rng:element>
              <rng:optional>
                <rng:ref name="msContents"/>
              </rng:optional>
              <!-- Äußeres -->
              <rng:optional>
                <rng:ref name="physDesc"/>
              </rng:optional>
              <!-- History -->
              <rng:optional>
                <rng:ref name="history"/>
              </rng:optional>
              <!-- addtitional -->
              <rng:optional>
                <rng:ref name="additional"/>
              </rng:optional>
              <!--  msParts in msPart -->
              <rng:zeroOrMore>
                <rng:ref name="msPart"/>
              </rng:zeroOrMore>
            </content>



            <!-- constraints for msPart sequence -->
            <constraintSpec ident="msDesc" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <sch:pattern id="msPart_fragment">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'fragment']">
                    <sch:assert test="not(
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'binding'])"> Only
                      msPart in the following order are allowed: binding, fragment, booklet, accMat, 
                      other </sch:assert>

                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <sch:pattern id="msPart_booklet">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet']">
                    <sch:assert test="not(
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'binding'] or 
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'fragment'])"> Only
                      msPart in the following order are allowed: binding, fragment, booklet, accMat, 
                      other </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <sch:pattern id="msPart_accMat">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'accMat']">
                    <sch:assert test="not(
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'binding'] or 
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'fragment'] or 
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet'])"> Only
                      msPart in the following order are allowed: binding, fragment, booklet, accMat, 
                      other </sch:assert>
                    
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <sch:pattern id="msPart_other">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'other']">
                    <sch:assert test="not(
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'binding'] or 
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'fragment'] or 
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet'] or 
                      following-sibling::tei:msPart[@type eq 'accMat'])"> Only
                      msPart in the following order are allowed: binding, fragment, booklet, accMat, 
                      other </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="xml:id" mode="change" usage="rec"/>
              <attDef ident="xml:lang" mode="change" usage="rec"/>
              <attDef ident="type" mode="replace" usage="rec">
                <valList type="closed" mode="replace">
                  <valItem ident="hsp:object">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">The TEI file represents (and contains) a <soCalled>Cultural
                        Object Document</soCalled></desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Die TEI-Datei repräsentiert und enthält ein <soCalled>Kultur
                        Objekt Dokument</soCalled>.</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="hsp:description">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">The TEI file represents (and contains) a manuscript
                      description</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Die TEI-Datei repräsentiert und enthält eine
                      Handschriftenbeschreibung</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="hsp:description_retro"/>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="subtype" mode="replace" usage="rec">
                <valList type="closed" mode="replace">
                  <valItem ident="medieval"/>
                  <valItem ident="illuminated"/>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="status" mode="replace" usage="rec">
                <valList type="closed" mode="replace">
                  <valItem ident="intern"/>
                  <valItem ident="extern"/>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
            </attList>
            <exemplum>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                <msDesc xml:id="__UUID__" xml:lang="de" status="intern" type="hsp:description"
                  subtype="medieval">
                  <!-- manuscript description -->
                </msDesc>
              </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification msIdentifier -->


          <!-- element specification msItem Komponente Abschnitt -->
          <elementSpec ident="msItem" mode="change" module="msdescription">
            <content>
              <!--
              * msItem has zeroOrMore msItem-Siblings
              * msItem has zeroOrMore children note, decoNote, msItem
              * msItem has zero or one textlang and if it has textLang it is its first child
              -->
              <elementRef key="textLang" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
              <alternate minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded">
                <elementRef key="note"/>
                <elementRef key="decoNote"/>
                <elementRef key="msItem"/>
                <elementRef key="index" minOccurs="0"/>
              </alternate>
            </content>
          </elementSpec>


          <!-- element specification msPart - Komponenten msPart -->
          <elementSpec ident="msPart" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <content>
              <!-- Komponente Identifikation -->
              <rng:element name="msIdentifier">
                <rng:optional>
                  <rng:ref name="settlement"/>
                </rng:optional>
                <rng:optional>
                  <rng:ref name="repository"/>
                </rng:optional>
                <rng:ref name="idno"/>
                <rng:optional>
                  <rng:element name="altIdentifier">
                    <rng:attribute name="type">
                      <rng:value>former</rng:value>
                    </rng:attribute>
                    <!-- one of the following 3 elements -->
                    <rng:oneOrMore>
                      <rng:optional>
                        <rng:ref name="settlement"/>
                      </rng:optional>
                      <rng:optional>
                        <rng:ref name="repository"/>
                      </rng:optional>
                      <rng:optional>
                        <rng:ref name="idno"/>
                      </rng:optional>
                    </rng:oneOrMore>
                  </rng:element>
                </rng:optional>
              </rng:element>


              <!-- choice für Komponente Kopf -->
              <rng:choice>
                <rng:choice>
                  <!-- Komponente Sonstiges,contains only one or more p elements -->
                  <rng:oneOrMore>
                    <rng:ref name="p"/>
                  </rng:oneOrMore>
                </rng:choice>
                <!-- Komponente Kopf für accMat, fragment, booklet, binding-->
                <rng:choice>
                  <rng:group>
                    <rng:element name="head">
                      <!-- ODD 0.7.0 sequence ist recommended, due to compatibility to 0.6.1 every sequence is allowed so far by interleaving  -->
                      <rng:interleave>
                        <!-- title norm -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_title</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>title</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:optional>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:optional>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:element>
                        <!-- title -->
                        <rng:element name="title">
                          <rng:optional>
                            <rng:text/>
                          </rng:optional>
                        </rng:element>
                        <!-- headline -->
                        <rng:element name="note">
                          <rng:attribute name="type">
                            <rng:value>headline</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:optional>
                            <rng:text/>
                          </rng:optional>
                        </rng:element>
                      </rng:interleave>
                      <rng:oneOrMore>
                        <!-- material -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_material</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>material</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:optional>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:optional>
                          </rng:element>
                          <!-- wdh -->
                          <rng:oneOrMore>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>material_type</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:element>
                          </rng:oneOrMore>
                        </rng:element>

                        <!-- measure -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_measure</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>measure</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:optional>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:optional>
                          </rng:element>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>measure_noOfLeaves</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:text/>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:element>

                        <!-- dimensions -->
                        <rng:oneOrMore>
                          <rng:element name="index">
                            <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                              <rng:value>norm_dimensions</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>dimensions</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:element>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>height</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:element>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>width</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:element>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>depth</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:element>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>dimensions_typeOfInformation</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:element>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:oneOrMore>

                        <!-- format -->
                        <rng:oneOrMore>
                          <rng:element name="index">
                            <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                              <rng:value>norm_format</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>format</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:element>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>format_typeOfInformation</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:element>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:oneOrMore>

                        <!-- origPlace -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_origPlace</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>origPlace</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:optional>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:optional>
                          </rng:element>
                          <!-- wdh. -->
                         <rng:oneOrMore>
                      <rng:element name="term">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:value>origPlace_norm</rng:value>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:optional>
                          <rng:attribute name="ref"/>
                        </rng:optional>
                        <rng:optional>
                          <rng:attribute name="key"/>
                        </rng:optional>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                    </rng:oneOrMore>
                        </rng:element>

                        <!-- origDate -->
                        <rng:oneOrMore>
                          <rng:element name="index">
                            <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                              <rng:value>norm_origDate</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>origDate</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:optional>
                                <rng:text/>
                              </rng:optional>
                            </rng:element>
                            <!-- als Block -->
                            <rng:group>
                              <rng:element name="term">
                                <rng:attribute name="type">
                                  <rng:value>origDate_notBefore</rng:value>
                                </rng:attribute>
                                <rng:optional>
                                  <rng:text/>
                                </rng:optional>
                              </rng:element>
                              <rng:element name="term">
                                <rng:attribute name="type">
                                  <rng:value>origDate_notAfter</rng:value>
                                </rng:attribute>
                                <rng:optional>
                                  <rng:text/>
                                </rng:optional>
                              </rng:element>
                              <rng:element name="term">
                                <rng:attribute name="type">
                                  <rng:value>origDate_type</rng:value>
                                </rng:attribute>
                                <rng:text/>
                              </rng:element>
                            </rng:group>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:oneOrMore>

                        <!-- textLang -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_textLang</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>textLang</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:optional>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:optional>
                          </rng:element>
                          <!-- wdh. -->
                          <rng:oneOrMore>
                            <rng:element name="term">
                              <rng:attribute name="type">
                                <rng:value>textLang-ID</rng:value>
                              </rng:attribute>
                              <rng:optional>
                                <rng:text/>
                              </rng:optional>
                            </rng:element>
                          </rng:oneOrMore>
                        </rng:element>

                        <!-- form -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_form</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>form</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:text/>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:element>

                        <!-- status -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_status</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>status</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:optional>
                              <rng:text/>
                            </rng:optional>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:element>

                        <!-- decoration -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_decoration</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>decoration</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:text/>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:element>

                        <!-- musicNotation -->
                        <rng:element name="index">
                          <rng:attribute name="indexName">
                            <rng:value>norm_musicNotation</rng:value>
                          </rng:attribute>
                          <rng:element name="term">
                            <rng:attribute name="type">
                              <rng:value>musicNotation</rng:value>
                            </rng:attribute>
                            <rng:text/>
                          </rng:element>
                        </rng:element>
                      </rng:oneOrMore>
                    </rng:element>

                    <!-- Inhalt  -->
                    <rng:optional>
                      <rng:ref name="msContents"/>
                    </rng:optional>
                    <!-- Äußeres -->
                    <rng:optional>
                      <rng:ref name="physDesc"/>
                    </rng:optional>
                    <!-- History -->
                    <rng:optional>
                      <rng:ref name="history"/>
                    </rng:optional>
                    <!-- addtitional -->
                    <rng:optional>
                      <rng:ref name="additional"/>
                    </rng:optional>
                    <!--  msParts in msPart -->
                    <rng:zeroOrMore>
                      <rng:ref name="msPart"/>
                    </rng:zeroOrMore>
                  </rng:group>
                </rng:choice>
              </rng:choice>
            </content>

            <constraintSpec ident="msPart" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <!-- constraint for msPart = booklet-->
                <sch:pattern id="booklet">
                  <!-- @form -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'form']">
                    <sch:assert test="(.='booklet') or (.='')"> If msPart @type = 'booklet', then
                      form should be 'booklet' or be empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!-- @material_type -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'material_type']">
                    <sch:assert test=".= ('','paper','linen','palm','papyrus','parchment','other')">
                      If type="material_type", text should contain 'paper', 'linen', 'palm',
                      'papyrus', 'parchment', 'other' or should stay empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- constraint for msPart = binding -->
                <sch:pattern id="binding">
                  <!-- @material_type -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'binding']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'material_type']">
                    <sch:assert
                      test=".=('','wood','leather','parchment','textile materials','gold','silver','copper','brass','other')"
                      > If msPart type="binding", material_type should contain
                      'wood','leather','parchment','textile
                      materials','gold','silver','copper','brass', 'other' or should stay empty
                    </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!-- @form -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'binding']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'form']">
                    <sch:assert test="(.='binding') or (.='')"> If msPart @type = 'binding', then
                      form should be 'binding' or be empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- constraint for msPart = accMat-->
                <sch:pattern id="accMat">
                  <!-- @material_type -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'accMat']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'material_type']">
                    <sch:assert test=".= ('','paper','linen','palm','papyrus','parchment','other')">
                      If type="accMat", material_type should contain 'paper', 'linen', 'palm',
                      'papyrus', 'parchment', 'other' or should stay empty. </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!-- @form -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'accMat']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'form']">
                    <sch:assert test=".=('','loose insert')"> If msPart @type = 'accMat',
                      then form should be 'loose insert' or be empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- constraint for msPart = fragment-->
                <sch:pattern id="fragment">
                  <!-- @material_type -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'fragment']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'material_type']">
                    <sch:assert test=".= ('','paper','linen','palm','papyrus','parchment','other')">
                      If msPart type="fragment" material_type should contain 'paper', 'linen',
                      'palm', 'papyrus', 'parchment', 'other' or should stay empty. </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <!-- @form -->
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'fragment']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'form']">
                    <sch:assert test="(.='fragment') or (.='')"> If msPart @type = 'fragment', then
                      form should be 'fragment' or be empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- constraint if msPart binding, fragment, accMat has KOK fragment or accMat or other  -->
                <sch:pattern id="msPartInmsPartStandard">
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'binding' or @type eq 'fragment' or @type eq 'accMat']/tei:msPart">
                    <sch:assert test="@type eq 'accMat' or @type eq 'fragment' or @type eq 'other'">
                      Only bindings, accMat and a fragment may contain further msParts with the
                      following types: accMat, fragment or other </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- constraint if msPart booklet has msPart fragment, booklet or accMat -->
                <sch:pattern id="msPartInmsPartBooklet">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet']/tei:msPart">
                    <sch:assert
                      test="@type eq 'fragment' or @type eq 'booklet' or @type eq 'accMat' or @type eq 'other'"
                      > Only booklets may contain further msParts with the following types: accMat
                      fragment, booklets and other</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- constraint for msPart in msPart @form -->
                <sch:pattern id="msPartInmsPartStandardForm">
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart/tei:msPart[@type eq 'fragment']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'form']">
                    <sch:assert test="(.='fragment') or (.='')"> If msPart @type = 'fragment', then
                      form should be 'fragment' or be empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart/tei:msPart[@type eq 'accMat']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'form']">
                    <sch:assert test="(.='accMat') or (.='')"> If msPart @type = 'accMat', then form
                      should be 'accMat' or be empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart/tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet']/tei:head/tei:index/tei:term[@type eq 'form']">
                    <sch:assert test="(.='booklet') or (.='')">If msPart @type = 'booklet' then form
                      should be 'booklet' or be empty </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- constraint for 'other'/Sonstiges -->
                <sch:pattern id="idnoKomponenteSonstiges">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'other']/tei:msIdentifier/tei:idno">
                    <sch:assert test=".=('Sonstiges')"> If msPart @type = 'other' then idno contains
                      'Sonstiges' </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <sch:pattern id="childKomponenteSonstiges">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'other']">
                    <sch:assert test="tei:p">msPart type="other" may only contain p Elements
                    </sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- only one msPart type="other" allowed-->
                <sch:pattern id="msPartoneP">
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet' or @type eq 'fragment' or @type eq 'binding' or @type eq 'accMat']">
                    <sch:assert test="count(tei:msPart[@type='other']) &lt; 2">only one msPart
                      type='other' is allowed in one msPart</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
                <!-- p not allowed in accMat, binding, fragment, booklet -->
                <sch:pattern id="msPartnoP">
                  <sch:rule
                    context="tei:msPart[@type eq 'booklet' or @type eq 'fragment' or @type eq 'binding' or @type eq 'accMat']">
                    <sch:report test=". != tei:p">booklet, fragment, binding, accMat may not contain a
                      p Element as direct child</sch:report>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>

            <!-- attList for msPart -->
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="type" usage="req" mode="replace">
                <valList type="closed">
                  <valItem ident="booklet">
                    <desc>description for a booklet</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="binding">
                    <desc>description of the binding</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="fragment">
                    <desc>description for a fragment</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="accMat">
                    <desc>description for accompanying material</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="other">
                    <desc>other</desc>
                  </valItem>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
            </attList>
          </elementSpec>


          <!-- had to delete att.anchoring for <note>, because there was a problem within the <head> element and <note type="headline"> -->
          <elementSpec ident="note" module="core" mode="change">
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="anchored" mode="delete"/>
              <attDef ident="targetEnd" mode="delete"/>
              <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="rec">
                <valList>
                  <valItem ident="text"/>
                  <valItem ident="music"/>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
            </attList>
            <exemplum>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                    <note type="text">description of the content of a manuscript</note>
                    <note type="music">description of the content of a musical notation</note>
                  </msItem>
                </msContents>
              </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification orgName Value List -->
          <elementSpec ident="orgName" mode="change" module="namesdates">
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="role" usage="rec" mode="replace">
                <datatype maxOccurs="unbounded">
                  <dataRef key="teidata.enumerated"/>
                </datatype>
                <valList type="semi">
                  <valItem ident="commissionedBy">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Auftraggeber</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="author">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Autor</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="bookbinder">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Buchbinder</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="mentionedIn">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Erwähnung</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="scribe">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Schreiber</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="previousOwner">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Vorbesitzer</desc>
                  </valItem>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="key" usage="rec" mode="change"/>
              <attDef ident="ref" usage="rec" mode="change"/>
            </attList>
            <exemplum>
              <p>Orte, Personen und Körperschaften werden, wenn möglich mit einem
                <att>role</att>-Attribut versehen, welche die Funktion in diesem Fall näher
                erläutert. </p>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> So gelten auch für die <orgName
                  role="previousOwner" ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/5036103-X">Staatsbibliothek zu
                  Berlin</orgName> die vorgegebenen Richtwerte. </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification persName value List -->
          <elementSpec ident="persName" mode="change" module="namesdates">
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="role" usage="rec" mode="replace">
                <datatype maxOccurs="unbounded">
                  <dataRef key="teidata.enumerated"/>
                </datatype>
                <valList type="semi">
                  <valItem ident="commissionedBy">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Auftraggeber</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="author">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Autor</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="bookbinder">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Buchbinder</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="mentionedIn">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Erwähnung</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="scribe">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Schreiber</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="previousOwner">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Vorbesitzer</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="translator">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Übersetzer</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="illuminator">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Illuminator</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="conservator">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Restaurator</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="other">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Sonstige Person</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="complementedBy">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Normdaten ergänzt von</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="editedBy">
                    <desc xml:lang="de">bearbeitet von</desc>
                  </valItem>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="key" usage="rec" mode="change"/>
              <attDef ident="ref" usage="rec" mode="change"/>
            </attList>
            <exemplum>
              <p>Orte, Personen und Körperschaften werden, wenn möglich mit einem
                <att>role</att>-Attribut versehen, welche die Funktion in diesem Fall näher
                erläutert. </p>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> So auch <persName
                  ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/118575449" key="31711049" role="author">Martin
                  Luther</persName>, der 1517 ... </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification physDesc - Komponente Äußeres und (Äußeres Kunst)-->
          <elementSpec ident="physDesc" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <content>
              <sequence>
                <classRef key="model.pLike" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
                <elementRef key="decoDesc" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
              </sequence>
            </content>
            <exemplum>
              <p>decoDesc may be used when specifying a description of some illuminated aspects of a
                manuscript, otherwise it is to be described in msContents</p>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                <phsyDesc>
                  <p>formal physical description</p>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="form"> insert the description of some illuminated aspects of a
                      manuscript here </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                </phsyDesc>
              </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification placeName value List -->
          <elementSpec ident="placeName" mode="change" module="namesdates">
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="role" usage="rec" mode="replace">
                <datatype maxOccurs="unbounded">
                  <dataRef key="teidata.enumerated"/>
                </datatype>
                <valList type="semi">
                  <valItem ident="origin">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">origin</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Entstehungsort</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="provenance">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">provenance</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Vorbesitz</desc>
                  </valItem>
                  <valItem ident="mentionedIn">
                    <desc xml:lang="en">mentionedIn</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="de">Erwähnung</desc>
                  </valItem>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="key" usage="rec" mode="change"/>
              <attDef ident="ref" usage="rec" mode="change"/>
            </attList>
            <exemplum>
              <p>Orte, Personen und Körperschaften werden, wenn möglich mit einem
                <att>role</att>-Attribut versehen, welche die Funktion in diesem Fall näher
                erläutert. </p>
              <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> Mit Sitz in <placeName
                  role="provenance" key="berlin" ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/4005728-8"
                  >Berlin</placeName>. </egXML>
            </exemplum>
          </elementSpec>


          <!-- Constraint für ref für  Digitalisate -->
          <elementSpec ident="ref" mode="change" module="core">
            <constraintSpec ident="ifTypeThenTarget" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <sch:pattern id="typeAndTarget">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:surrogates/tei:bibl/tei:ref">
                    <sch:assert test="(@type and @target)">if ref has a type a target is
                      required</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
            <constraintSpec ident="ref_check" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <sch:pattern>
                  <sch:rule context="tei:ref">
                    <sch:assert test="@target or @type">You must provide either @target or
                      @type.</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification for repository -->
          <elementSpec ident="repository" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="key" mode="change" usage="opt">
                <desc xml:lang="en">contains the hsp-uuid of the repository</desc>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="ref" mode="change" usage="opt"> </attDef>
            </attList>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification for settlement -->
          <elementSpec ident="settlement" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="key" mode="change" usage="opt">
                <desc xml:lang="en">contains the hsp-uuid of the settlement</desc>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="ref" mode="change" usage="opt"> </attDef>
            </attList>
          </elementSpec>

          <!-- element specification surrogates in teiheader/sourceDesc/msDesc/additional added 01-10-2021-->
          <elementSpec ident="surrogates" module="msdescription" mode="change">
            <content>
              <rng:zeroOrMore>
                <rng:element name="bibl">
                  <rng:zeroOrMore>
                    <rng:element name="ref">
                      <rng:attribute name="type">
                        <rng:choice>
                          <rng:value>hsp:object</rng:value>
                          <rng:value>manifest</rng:value>
                          <rng:value>thumbnail</rng:value>
                          <rng:value>other</rng:value>
                          <rng:value>completeness</rng:value>
                          <rng:value>sourceType</rng:value>
                          <rng:value>digitalisationType</rng:value>
                          <rng:value>captureType</rng:value>
                        </rng:choice>
                      </rng:attribute>
                      <rng:attribute name="target"/>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:zeroOrMore>
                  <rng:zeroOrMore>
                    <rng:group>
                      <rng:element name="orgName">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:choice>
                            <rng:value>hostInstitution</rng:value>
                            <rng:value>digitalisingInstitution</rng:value>
                          </rng:choice>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:attribute name="ref"/>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                      <rng:element name="placeName">
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:choice>
                            <rng:value>hostInstitution</rng:value>
                            <rng:value>digitalisingInstitution</rng:value>
                          </rng:choice>
                        </rng:attribute>
                        <rng:attribute name="ref"/>
                        <rng:text/>
                      </rng:element>
                    </rng:group>
                  </rng:zeroOrMore>
                  <rng:zeroOrMore>
                    <rng:element name="date">
                      <rng:optional>
                        <rng:attribute name="when"/>
                        <rng:attribute name="type">
                          <rng:choice>
                            <rng:value>published</rng:value>
                            <rng:value>digitalised</rng:value>
                          </rng:choice>
                        </rng:attribute>
                      </rng:optional>
                      <rng:text/>
                    </rng:element>
                  </rng:zeroOrMore>
                </rng:element>
              </rng:zeroOrMore>
            </content>
          </elementSpec>




          <!-- ########################################## classModifications ###################################################### -->
          <specGrp xml:id="classmods">
            <classSpec ident="att.global" mode="change" module="tei" type="atts">
              <attList>
                <attDef ident="xml:space" mode="delete"/>
                <attDef ident="xml:base" mode="delete"/>
              </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.global.rendition" mode="change" module="tei" type="atts">
              <attList>
                <!--<attDef ident="rend" mode="delete"/>-->
                <attDef ident="style" mode="delete"/>
              </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.fragmentable" mode="delete" module="tei" type="atts"/>
            <classSpec ident="att.divLike" mode="delete" module="tei" type="atts"/>
            <classSpec ident="att.declaring" mode="delete" module="tei" type="atts"/>
            <classSpec ident="att.written" mode="delete" module="tei" type="atts"/>
            <classSpec ident="att.declarable" mode="change" module="tei" type="atts">
              <attList>
                <attDef ident="default" mode="delete"/>
              </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.editLike" mode="change" module="tei" type="atts">
              <attList>
                <attDef ident="instant" mode="delete"/>
              </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.personal" module="tei" mode="change" type="atts">
              <attList>
                <attDef ident="full" mode="delete"/>
              </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.docStatus" module="tei" mode="change" type="atts">
              <attList>
                <attDef ident="status" mode="delete"/>
              </attList>
            </classSpec>
          </specGrp>

          <!-- ####################################### Include XInclude into our schema ############################################################# -->
          <elementSpec ident="include" ns="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" mode="add">
            <desc xml:lang="en" versionDate="2014-01-12">The W3C XInclude element</desc>
            <classes>
              <memberOf key="model.common"/>
              <memberOf key="model.teiHeaderPart"/>
            </classes>
            <content>
              <elementRef key="fallback" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
            </content>
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="href">
                <desc xml:lang="en" versionDate="2014-01-12">pointer to the resource being
                  included</desc>
                <datatype>
                  <dataRef key="teidata.pointer"/>
                </datatype>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="parse" usage="opt">
                <defaultVal>xml</defaultVal>
                <valList type="closed">
                  <valItem ident="xml"/>
                  <valItem ident="text"/>
                </valList>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="xpointer" usage="opt">
                <datatype>
                  <dataRef key="teidata.text"/>
                </datatype>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="encoding" usage="opt">
                <datatype>
                  <dataRef key="teidata.text"/>
                </datatype>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="accept" usage="opt">
                <datatype>
                  <dataRef key="teidata.text"/>
                </datatype>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="accept-charset" usage="opt">
                <datatype>
                  <dataRef key="teidata.text"/>
                </datatype>
              </attDef>
              <attDef ident="accept-language" usage="opt">
                <datatype>
                  <dataRef key="teidata.text"/>
                </datatype>
              </attDef>
            </attList>
          </elementSpec>
          <elementSpec ident="fallback" ns="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" mode="add">
            <desc xml:lang="en" versionDate="2014-01-12">Wrapper for fallback elements if an
              XInclude fails</desc>
            <content>
              <alternate>
                <textNode/>
                <anyElement/>
              </alternate>
            </content>
          </elementSpec>


          <!-- ##########################################################  global constraints  ############################################################ -->


          <!-- check: further needed?
          <elementSpec ident="origDate" mode="change" module="msdescription">
            <constraintSpec ident="origdate_check" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <sch:pattern name="date_values">
                  <sch:rule context="tei:origDate">
                    <sch:assert test="@when or (@notAfter and @notBefore) or (@from and @to)">You
                      must provide either @when or @to/@from, or @notAfter/@notBefore.</sch:assert>
                  </sch:rule>
                </sch:pattern>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
          </elementSpec>-->

          <!-- a manuscript must have one or more languages  -->
          <elementSpec ident="textLang" module="core" mode="change">
            <constraintSpec ident="textLang.check" scheme="schematron">
              <constraint>
                <!--<sch:rule context="//tei:msContents">
                  <sch:assert test="descendant::tei:textLang" role="warn">A manuscript should have
                    one or more languages recorded in a textLang element. For manuscripts with no
                    linguistic content use code 'zxx'. If the language is undetermined use the code
                    'und'.</sch:assert>
                </sch:rule>-->
                <!--<sch:rule context="//tei:textLang">
                  <sch:assert test="@mainLang and string-length(normalize-space(string())) gt 0"
                    role="error">The predominant language must be recorded in using a code in a
                    mainLang attribute (and an otherLang attribute if there are other languages) and
                    described as text within the textLang element.</sch:assert>
                </sch:rule>-->
                <sch:rule
                  context="//tei:textLang/@mainLang | //tei:textLang/@otherLangs | //@xml:lang">
                  <sch:assert
                    test="every $code in tokenize(., ' ') satisfies matches($code, '^[a-z]{2,3}(-|$)')"
                    role="error">Codes in <sch:value-of select="name(.)"/> attributes must conform
                    to BCP 47 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47), starting with an ISO 639 code for
                    the language, then optionally further codes for the script (ISO 15924), region,
                    transliteration, etc.</sch:assert>
                </sch:rule>
              </constraint>
            </constraintSpec>
            <attList>
              <attDef ident="mainLang" mode="change" usage="req"/>
            </attList>
          </elementSpec>

        </schemaSpec>
      </div>
    </body>
    <back> </back>
  </text>
</TEI>
